article.headline: Illinois St. 70, Evansville 68
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. -- Osiris Eldridge scored 18 points, including the game-winning layup with just over one second left, to lead Illinois State to a 70-68 win over Evansville on Wednesday night in the Missouri Valley Conference. The Purple Aces (15-9, 7-7) trailed 45-24 at the break but rallied to tie the game at 68 with 13 seconds left. But Eldridge nailed the layup for the win after a 30-second timeout. Emmanuel Holloway scored 12 for the Redbirds (20-5, 9-5), who shot 51 percent from the field. Brandon Sampay had 10 points and eight rebounds and Dinma Odiakosa had 10 points. Shy Ely had 24 points to lead Evansville (15-9, 7-7), who shot 52 percent overall. Nate Garner had 13 points and 10 rebounds. Evansville outscored the Redbirds 42-20 in the paint. Illinois State outrebounded the Purple Aces 30-25.
